<task id="004" project="ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2">
  <metadata>
    <title>B4 — Re-deploy predict-matter-cost@v1 to Spaarke Dev with action references</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <wave>B</wave>
    <estimated-effort>30m</estimated-effort>
    <tags>deploy, dataverse, predict-matter-cost, unblock-synthesis</tags>
    <dependencies>002, 003</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <rigor>STANDARD</rigor>
    <wave-item>B4</wave-item>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Run Deploy-Playbook.ps1 with the updated predict-matter-cost.playbook.json to recreate the playbook in Spaarke Dev with proper action-code references and sprk_isactive=true on all nodes. The existing playbook can either be (a) updated in place via the script's -Force flag if supported, or (b) deleted and recreated. Either approach must result in 8 active nodes wired to the 6 INSIGHTS.* action rows plus the existing AgentService synthesis action.
  </prompt>

  <role>Operator + Spaarke deployment specialist.</role>

  <goal>
    predict-matter-cost@v1 live in Spaarke Dev with: 8 sprk_playbooknode rows, each sprk_isactive=true, each carrying an action-code reference (FK to the matching sprk_analysisaction row). PlaybookExecutionEngine builds an 8-node execution graph at invocation time. Lint check from task 003 runs as part of the deploy and passes.
  </prompt>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="script">scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1 (lint-enhanced via task 003)</file>
    <file purpose="config">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Insights/Playbooks/predict-matter-cost.playbook.json (updated via task 002)</file>
    <file purpose="env">Spaarke Dev — must be az-logged in to the target tenant</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="r1">Spaarke Dev only (single-tenant per D-52); no prod deploy in Wave B</constraint>
    <constraint source="task-003">Lint check must pass before any Dataverse writes</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Verify env">az login; confirm correct subscription + Dataverse env</step>
    <step order="2" name="Inspect existing playbook">Query Dataverse for current predict-matter-cost@v1 + its nodes; document state (likely 8 nodes with sprk_isactive=false from the original r1 deploy, now manually patched)</step>
    <step order="3" name="Decide update strategy">Either delete + recreate (cleaner) or -Force update (if script supports). Document choice in handoff notes.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Run Deploy-Playbook.ps1">With the updated JSON; lint check from task 003 runs first; if it passes, Dataverse writes proceed</step>
    <step order="5" name="Verify post-deploy state">Query Dataverse: 8 sprk_playbooknode rows; all sprk_isactive=true; each carries an action-code reference; references resolve to the rows from task 001</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="pwsh">Deploy-Playbook.ps1 execution</tool>
    <tool name="az">Auth + env selection</tool>
    <tool name="mcp__dataverse__read_query">Verify post-deploy state</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="dataverse-state">predict-matter-cost@v1 live with 8 properly-wired active nodes</output>
    <output type="notes">projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/notes/handoffs/wave-b4-deploy-trace.md (deploy log + verification queries)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">8 sprk_playbooknode rows live for predict-matter-cost@v1</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All 8 nodes have sprk_isactive=true</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Each node carries an action-code reference resolving to a row from task 001 (or the existing AgentService synthesis action for the synthesis node)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">PlaybookExecutionEngine builds an 8-active-node execution graph (verified via /api/insights/ask test in task 005)</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
